# Accessibility Standards (WCAG AA)

## Color Contrast Minimums

- Normal text (< 18px / < 14px bold): **4.5:1** contrast ratio
- Large text (≥ 18px / ≥ 14px bold): **3:1** contrast ratio
- Use semantic color tokens that are pre-verified:
  - Text on white: `--color-neutral-700` or darker ✓
  - Primary text: `--color-primary-700` on white ✓ (8.59:1)
  - Error text: `--color-error-600` on white ✓ (4.63:1)

## Interactive Elements

Every interactive element MUST:
- Be focusable via keyboard
- Show a visible focus ring using `var(--focus-ring)`
- Have an accessible name (`aria-label`, `aria-labelledby`, or visible label)

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — no accessible name
<button onClick={close}>✕</button>

// ✅ GOOD
<button onClick={close} aria-label="Close dialog">✕</button>
```

## Form Fields

Every form input MUST have an associated `<label>`:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — no label
<input type="email" placeholder="Email" />

// ✅ GOOD — use FormField wrapper
<FormField label="Email" htmlFor="email">
  <Input id="email" type="email" />
</FormField>
```

Error states require both visual indication AND `aria-invalid` + `aria-describedby`:

```tsx
<Input error aria-invalid="true" aria-describedby="email-error" />
<p id="email-error" role="alert">Invalid email address.</p>
```

## Images

All `<img>` elements MUST have descriptive `alt` text. Empty `alt=""` is only acceptable for purely decorative images.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<img src="/logo.svg" />

// ✅ GOOD
<img src="/logo.svg" alt="Acme Inc." />
```

## Accessibility Testing

Every component MUST include an `.a11y.test.tsx` with zero violations:

```tsx
it('has no accessibility violations', async () => {
  const { container } = render(<Button variant="primary">Submit</Button>);
  expect(await axe(container)).toHaveNoViolations();
});
```
